transcript.message: Yes, that's correct. The Entertainer. Now, could you please provide a high-level description of this matter?

Yeah so we worked with The Entertainer on their move in to compete with Chinese, the Chinese directly who were undercutting the UK markets. So we worked on a new route to market from Finland where The Entertainer was setting up a new toy factory and supply chain. And we were the people who were leading on the cross-border EU elements in terms of whether it was possible to undercut the Chinese based on the loophole of Finland to UK child protection regulation, which allowed for not only zero tax, but a rebate back into the business system.
That sounds like a complex and interesting matter. Could you tell me more about the specific role your department played in this initiative?
Yes. So we were brought in to look at the cross-border elements of the tax and consultancy opportunity. That was the role we played.
Thank you. And could you describe the specific work done on this matter in the previous twelve months, keeping in mind that the submission guidelines require us to focus on this timeframe?

Yes. So basically, we were focused in on the finished part of the challenge in the last 12 months. This meant going to Helsinki and finding out what potential opportunities there might be for the logistics and supply chain elements, and in particular, focusing on what pay port you might need in order to get the tax rebates.

And just to confirm, as this is a new matter, is it okay to assume that the work you've outlined, focusing on the Finland logistics and supply chain elements and identifying potential tax rebate opportunities, was all undertaken in the previous twelve months?
